  "prompt": "Can students leave after MS in direct PhD programs at IIT's?",
  "response": "In most IIT direct PhD programs, students cannot simply leave after completing their MS portion. Typically:\n\n1. Direct PhD programs have a structured pathway:\n- Students are admitted directly to the doctoral program\n- They complete coursework and MS requirements\n- Must continue towards PhD completion\n\n2. Conditions for leaving:\n- Some programs might allow exit with MS degree\n- Depends on specific department and institute policies\n- Often requires academic review and approval\n\n3. General expectations:\n- Students are expected to complete full PhD program\n- Commitment is usually for entire doctoral research\n- Early exit may have academic or financial implications\n\n4. Recommendations:\n- Check specific department guidelines\n- Discuss options with academic advisor\n- Understand program's specific rules and expectations\n\n5. Potential scenarios:\n- Some departments might permit MS exit with certain conditions\n- Others may require continuing in the doctoral track\n- Individual institute policies vary\n\nFor precise details, it's best to:\n- Contact specific IIT department\n- Review official program documentation\n- Consult academic advisors directly",
